                  "pageTitle": "Duplex Bond",
                  "pageId": 1580998,
                  "revisionId": 2776363,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "Clones are completely invulnerable to any form of damage, and can only die after their listed lifespan has elapsed since they were created."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "pageTitle": "Duplex Bond",
                  "pageId": 1580998,
                  "revisionId": 2776363,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "Despite being invincible, enemies will still have their aggro drawn to them and attempt to fight them."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "pageTitle": "Duplex Bond",
                  "pageId": 1580998,
                  "revisionId": 2776363,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "Cloned Sentinels will float toward enemies rather than sticking to the player, drawing some aggro away from the player as a result."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "pageTitle": "Duplex Bond",
                  "pageId": 1580998,
                  "revisionId": 2776363,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "Invisibility applied to the player is only shared with the main Companion, it is not applied to any summoned/spawned clones and they will remain visible to distract enemy fire."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "pageTitle": "Duplex Bond",
                  "pageId": 1580998,
                  "revisionId": 2776363,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "Since the clones can only use basic attacks, they benefit greatly from Beast Claws Mods . They can use all the claw mods and deal full damage with them."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "pageTitle": "Duplex Bond",
                  "pageId": 1580998,
                  "revisionId": 2776363,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "While clones cannot activate any abilities, they can still be useful for spreading status effects, especially if buffed by external sources (e.g. Nourish )."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "pageTitle": "Duplex Bond",
                  "pageId": 1580998,
                  "revisionId": 2776363,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "Clones will not benefit from, nor trigger, most mods on the Companion itself. Tested examples include but are not limited to: Momentous Bond , Astral Bond , Vicious Bond , Contagious Bond , Seismic Bond , Tandem Bond , Hunter Recovery , Synth Deconstruct , Fired Up , Hunter Recovery , and Energy Generator ."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "pageTitle": "Duplex Bond",
                  "pageId": 1580998,
                  "revisionId": 2776363,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "Hard Engage is an exception, as MOA (Companion) clones will gain the ability to use melee attacks."
                }
              },
